00:13:07,956 --> 00:13:08,816
And what do I mean by that?

258
00:13:09,576 --> 00:13:11,277
All of your previous skills are still useful.

259
00:13:13,378 --> 00:13:15,800
Your player ranking of every single player in the world

260
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,000
has not changed at all.

261
00:13:18,442 --> 00:13:21,985
you still have the same world champion.

262
00:13:22,025 --> 00:13:23,607
You still have all of the chess books.

263
00:13:23,627 --> 00:13:24,968
You still have all the opening moves.

264
00:13:25,348 --> 00:13:27,170
You still have every little bit of effort

265
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:28,812
and every little bit of skill that you

266
00:13:28,832 --> 00:13:30,553
would want to acquire to win chess.

267
00:13:31,094 --> 00:13:34,157
That's all still existing in the game of rando chess.

268
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:39,923
And the point to that is that this skill versus luck

269
00:13:40,483 --> 00:13:42,005
is actually a false dichotomy.

270
00:13:43,265 --> 00:13:46,927
Really, you should think of it more as a graph where

271
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:49,628
you have a certain amount of skill in games

272
00:13:49,728 --> 00:13:51,029
and a certain amount of luck in games.

273
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:56,812
And games can be sort of placed anywhere on that.

274
00:13:58,894 --> 00:14:04,617
Go has a lot of skill, as does poker.

275
00:14:05,017 --> 00:14:05,978
But poker has more luck.

276
00:14:09,238 --> 00:14:11,179
So what did change in Rando Chess?

277
00:14:11,199 --> 00:14:12,340
The game clearly changed.

278
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:15,661
Skill, by a reasonable definition of it, didn't change.

279
00:14:16,621 --> 00:14:19,342
But what did change was, as luck went up,

280
00:14:20,102 --> 00:14:21,343
